          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Deposited on gold coated quartz",
                " disks, U-235 was evaporated as U-F(4).",
                " Isotopic composition in per-cent,",
                "  U-234   1.0812 +- 0.0020,   U-235   93.336 +- 0.010,",
                "  U-236   0.2027 +- 0.0006,   U-238    5.380 +- 0.005,",
                " in U235-F(4) samples (U4,U5 NBS-930).",
                " The amounts of U-235 on the foils were determined",
                " from precise low-geometry alpha-counting.",
                " The neutron induced fission rates were checked as a",
                " relative control.",
                " Weights of U-samples (weights in micro-g U-235) are",
                " 1597.8 +- 2.8 (sample U4), 3228.0 +- 5.7 (sample U5).",
                " The determination of the specific activity of U-sample",
                " (nbs-930) is heavily dependent on the alpha-half-life",
                " of U-234."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "       Fission fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " A final value for the 2200 m/sec fission cross-section",
                " of 92-U-235 was obtained, making use of a carefully",
                " redetermined value of the U-234 alpha-half-life of",
                " (2.446 +- 0.002)*E+5 years at CBNM.",
                " The thermal fission cross section of U-235 as",
                " recommended by the IAEA-review (Hanna et al.,Atomic",
                " Energy Review,VII,4(1963)3.) may be too low by a few",
                " barns.",
                ".The Westcott g(F) values for 20.44 deg-C Maxwell-",
                " distribution is  g(F) = 0.9780 +- 0.0010."
              ]
            }
          ],
