          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Deposited on gold coated quartz disks,",
                " Pu-239 was deposited as Pu-acetate by electrospraying.",
                " Isotopic composition in per-cent,",
                "  Pu-239   99.979, Pu-240   0.02, Pu-241   0.001,",
                " in Pu-acetate-samples (TP442-1 and TP442-3).",
                " The amounts of U-235 and Pu-239 on the foils were",
                " determined from precise low-geometry alpha-counting.",
                " The neutron induced fission rates were checked as a",
                " relative control.",
                " Weights of Pu-samples (weights in micro-g Pu-239) are",
                " 267.72 +- 0.43 (sample TP442-1) and 1010.40 +- 1.62",
                " (sample TP442-3)."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "PART-DET": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "FF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "       Fission fragments."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " The separation between the pile-up tail produced by",
                " the alpha-particles of Pu-239 and the fission fragment",
                " pulse-height distribution was very good.",
                " The Westcott g(F) values for 20.44 deg-C Maxwell-",
                " distribution is",
                " g(F)= 1.0540 +- 0.00018(BR2), 1.0566 +- 0.018(Linac).",
                " For Pu-239, the present results seem to confirm",
                " completely the recommended values (Hanna et al.,Atomic",
                " Energy Review,VII,4(1969)3 )."
              ]
            }
          ],
